Here is a copy of this script:
=======================================================================
#!/bin/zsh

# Build SPEC CPU tools for MacOS X
export PATH=/usr/bin:/bin

# Most of the scary settings below are to select a not-necessarily-native SDK

# For Universal binaries, uncomment the line below:
export SDK=/Developer/SDKs/MacOSX10.4u.sdk
export ARCH="i686 ppc"

# The default GCC (4.2.1) doesn't have headers in the 10.4u SDK
export CC=gcc-4.0
export CXX=g++-4.0
export CPP="$CC -isysroot $SDK -E"

# We want 10.4, but the cross-arch compile doesn't really work, so just stick
# with the native 32-bit architecture.
export ARCH=i686

export CONFIGFLAGS="--disable-dependency-tracking"
export CFLAGS="-isysroot $SDK -mmacosx-version-min=10.4"
export LDFLAGS="-Wl,-syslibroot,$SDK -mmacosx-version-min=10.4"
export CPPFLAGS=-no-cpp-precomp
export XZCFLAGS="-O3 -D_FILE_OFFSET_BITS=64"
export MD5CFLAGS="-O3 -D_FILE_OFFSET_BITS=64"
PERLFLAGS="-Dcc=$CC -Acc=-isysroot -Acc=$SDK -Acc=-mmacosx-version-min=10.4"
PERLFLAGS="$PERLFLAGS -Doptimize=-O3 -Accflags=-fno-stack-protector"
for i in $ARCH; do
  PERLFLAGS="$PERLFLAGS -Accflags=-arch -Accflags=$i"
  PERLFLAGS="$PERLFLAGS -Aldflags=-arch -Aldflags=$i"
  PERLFLAGS="$PERLFLAGS -Alddlflags=-arch -Alddlflags=$i"
  CFLAGS="$CFLAGS -arch $i"
  LDFLAGS="$LDFLAGS -arch $i"
done
PERLFLAGS="$PERLFLAGS -Aldflags=-Wl,-syslibroot,$SDK"
PERLFLAGS="$PERLFLAGS -Alddlflags=-Wl,-syslibroot,$SDK"
PERLFLAGS="$PERLFLAGS -Uloclib -Dlibpth=/usr/lib"
# Without this, Configure finds libutil, which is in the 10.5 and 10.6 SDKs,
# but not 10.4
PERLFLAGS="$PERLFLAGS -Dlibs=-ldl -Alibs=-lm -Alibs=-lc"

export PERLFLAGS
export CFLAGS
export LDFLAGS

echo PATH is $PATH
echo
echo I am
id
echo
echo This system is
uname -a
echo
echo The compiler I will use today is
$CC -v
echo
echo Here is a copy of this script:
echo =======================================================================
cat $0
echo =======================================================================
echo

cd tools/src
time ./buildtools

echo
echo Small proof of success:
echo
cd ../..
. ./shrc
specperl -V
echo
touch SUMS.tools
runspec -V
echo
runspec --test
echo
echo Done
=======================================================================
